## 1.1 NPK CONTENTS AND MINERALS REPLACEMENT VALUE

**Replacement Value: \$113-\$330. Based on Indonesia CIF Prices October
2025.**

**CFI contains: N 4.32% \| P 3.05% \| K 2.72%**

CFI\'s product includes natural minerals which provide nutrients to the
plants and the soil\'s microbiome. The following tables summarize the
comparable synthetic mineral costs needed to match the exact
plant-available N, P and K supplied by 1 tonne of CFI\'s product, under
both very good and poor agricultural management practices.

Nitrogen loss involves leaching and Phosphorus becomes fixated in the
soils; requiring more synthetic minerals applied in order to reach the
target plant availability. ***See*** detailed explanations in Section
1.2 and 1.3.

**Much of the loss/fixation can be limited with Very Good Agricultural
Practices (VGAM)**

