**4.1.1 Organic Fertilizer Market**

Indonesia produces 800,000 tons of organic fertilizer per year, of which
500,000 are subsidized.¹⁰⁷

> • Market value 2024/2025 - circa \$2.2 billion
>
> • CAGR 6% and 11%
>
> • Projected to reach \$3.1 billion in 2030 (6% CAGR)

*\"The primary driver of Indonesia\'s organic fertilizers market is the
growing consumer demand for organic food products. The government\'s
efforts to promote organic farming practices are also driving the demand
for organic fertilizers.\"¹⁰⁸*

**4.2 Government Subsidies and Policy Framework**

Government subsidies play a critical role in Indonesia\'s fertilizer
market - \$1.71 billion in 2024.¹⁰⁹

> • Subsidies expected to reach \$2.73 billion in 2025, driven by
> government food security
>
> • Applies to small holder farmers \<2 hectares farms and local
> production

