**Application of Organic Fertiliser**

Optimal application recommendations vary by crop and region: traditional
manure at 20--30 tons per hectare annually, organic fertilizer at 15--60
tons per hectare, nitrogen-based applications at 150--200 kg N per
hectare, and maximum safe limits at 40 tons per hectare to prevent
pollution. Indonesian practices generally align with these standards,
adapting to local climate and cropping systems.

**Comparative Insights**

Indonesia's organic farmland represents only 1.5 percent of the global
total, and its usage intensity per hectare is moderately below the
global average, indicating opportunities to increase adoption and
intensification. Government support through subsidies and policy
initiatives has driven an 11 percent projected CAGR from 2025 to 2031,
outpacing global growth rates and underscoring Indonesia's emerging role
in sustainable agriculture.

**Free Market Organic Fertiliser (depending on nutritional value) ranges
between \$110 - \$150 / ton for Bulk/Loose and + \$200 for Pelletized.**

