**4.7.2 Strategic Recommendations**

> 1\. AVOID Subsidized Segment - Government price controls (\$40/ton)
> create unbeatable floor
>
> 2\. SKIP Economy Segment - Herbafarm\'s 11x markup at \$30/ton is
> anomalous; farmers conditioned to unrealistic expectations
>
> 3\. TARGET Mid-Tier Segment (\$135-250/ton) - Healthy 1.3-2.0x markups
> are sustainable; NASA, KURNIAGANIK demonstrate viable positioning
>
> 4\. DISRUPT Premium Segment - FERTINDO/PALMO/PORNAS at 0.8-1.3x markup
> are VULNERABLE; price exceeds nutrient value
>
> 5\. EXPLOIT Functionality Gap - NO competitor combines NPK + protein +
> chitin effectively; Shrimp Shell LOF proves \$350/ton chitin premium
> but requires separate NPK purchase

