**6.5 Coffee Waste and Emissions**

**6.5.1 Waste Generation Volumes**

Coffee processing generates massive volumes of organic waste, creating
both environmental challenges and opportunities for valorization:¹⁷⁸

> • Total waste volume: 23-40 million tons annually globally
>
> • Waste-to-production ratio: 2.2-4 kg waste per kg coffee beans
>
> • Cherry processing: 575 kg waste per ton cherries (pulp and mucilage)
>
> • Coffee pulp: 57.5% of cherry weight (80-85% moisture content)
>
> • Factory example: 27,500 tons coffee/year generates 6,515 tons dry
> waste

