**6.6 Carbon Footprint Analysis**

**6.6.1 Emission Factors**

Coffee production and processing contribute significantly to global
greenhouse gas emissions:¹⁸⁰

> • 1 kg roasted coffee can emit up to 40 kg CO₂e (cradle to consumer)
>
> • Global coffee carbon footprint: \~300 million tons CO₂e/year
>
> • Methane (CH₄) from decomposing pulp: 82× more potent than CO₂
> (20-year GWP)
>
> • Methane (CH₄): 28× more potent than CO₂ (100-year GWP)
>
> • Fertilizer production/use: 40-50% of on-farm emissions

