**6.9 Chitin Benefits from BSF Larvae**

BSF larvae contain significant chitin content (4.4% in CFI product),
providing unique benefits for coffee production beyond traditional NPK
nutrition:¹⁸⁶

**6.9.1 Disease Suppression Mechanisms**

> • Natural pest resistance: Chitin triggers systemic acquired
> resistance (SAR) in plants
>
> • Coffee Berry Disease (CBD) control: 45-60% reduction in infection
> rates observed
>
> • Coffee Leaf Rust (CLR) suppression: 35-50% reduction in severity
>
> • Root-knot nematode control: 65% reduction in galling index

**6.9.2 Soil Health Enhancement**

> • Microbial activity: 180% increase in beneficial chitinase-producing
> bacteria
>
> • Water retention: 25% improvement in soil water-holding capacity
>
> • Soil structure: Enhanced aggregation and reduced erosion
>
> • Carbon sequestration: 1.2 tons C/ha/year additional storage

