# 7.2 INDONESIAN PALM OIL INDUSTRY

Indonesia\'s palm oil industry is crucial for national economic
development, contributing 3.5% of GDP and employing 16 million people
directly and indirectly.²⁰⁰

## 7.2.1 Production Volumes and Economic Importance

Indonesia\'s palm oil industry operates at massive scale:²⁰¹

• Total planted area: 16.8 million hectares

• CPO production: 46.8 million tonnes annually

• FFB processed: 234 million tonnes annually

• Export value: \$28.5 billion (2023)

• Number of mills: 888 operational

• Smallholder participation: 40% of planted area

## 7.2.2 Waste Generation and Emissions

Indonesia generates approximately 100 million tonnes of palm oil biomass
waste annually. CFI is focused on the ZERO-VALUE waste - the Empty Fruit
Bunch (EFB), which is mostly discarded in piles and involves open
decomposition creating massive, unreported GHG emissions.

**The EFB\'s emissions are estimated at 38.9 Million Tonnes of CO₂e (GWP
100 Years) based on IPCC AR5.**

