# 7.4 INDONESIA BIOETHANOL FROM EFB PROGRAM

The Indonesian government has established comprehensive incentives for
bioethanol production from palm waste, yet commercial viability remains
elusive.²⁰⁷

## 7.4.1 Government Incentives and Mandates

**Financial Incentives:²³⁶**

• Tax holiday: 5-20 years corporate income tax exemption

• Import duty exemption: Machinery and equipment

• Super tax deduction: 300% for R&D expenses

• Investment allowance: 30% of investment as tax deduction

• Land and building tax reduction: 50-100% for 5 years

## 7.4.2 Technical and Economic Challenges

***CRITICAL REALITY: Zero commercial-scale EFB-to-ethanol facilities
exist globally despite decades of research and billions in
investment.²³⁷***

