# Palm Oil Industry EFB and PKF Waste Management Analysis

*October 2025*

## Summary

Indonesia is the world\'s largest palm oil producer, generating
approximately 28-31 million tonnes of Empty Fruit Bunches (EFB) and
substantial volumes of Palm Kernel Fiber (PKF) and Palm Kernel Shell
(PKS) annually. The palm oil industry faces significant waste management
challenges, with traditional practices of burning or direct mulching
giving way to more sustainable approaches including composting, biogas
production, mushroom cultivation, and biomass energy generation.

This report provides a comprehensive analysis of waste management
practices across Indonesia\'s major palm oil companies, with detailed
profiles of Golden Agri Resources (GAR/Sinar Mas) and Wilmar
International, which together account for a significant portion of
Indonesia\'s palm oil milling capacity.

