# 8.7 Strategic Recommendations for CFI

The palm oil buyer landscape presents exceptional opportunity for CFI\'s
BSF-based organic fertilizer solution. With \$33.36 billion in disclosed
sustainability commitments and only 4.4% of companies specifically
targeting synthetic fertilizer reduction, CFI is uniquely positioned to
capture significant market share^³²⁵^.

**IMMEDIATE ENGAGEMENT PRIORITIES:**

-   **Unilever:** 23 projects explicitly reducing synthetic fertiliser,
    €1B Climate Fund^³¹³^

-   **PepsiCo:** Active IDH Aceh-Tamiang pilot, 3.5M acres, 55 demo
    farms^³¹⁴^

-   **Nestlé:** Established Aceh Hub, CHF 1.2B regenerative budget,
    co-investment model^³¹⁵^

-   **Wilmar:** Fertiliser management programs across MY/ID/Africa,
    direct operations^³¹⁶^

-   **J.M. Smucker/ADM:** Explicit fertiliser efficiency targets, 20k
    acres/yr, 3-year program^³¹⁷^

The convergence of EUDR implementation (December 30, 2025), CSRD Wave 1
reporting requirements (active now), and corporate regenerative
agriculture investments creates optimal conditions for BSF organic
fertilizer adoption. CFI\'s proven technology, Indonesian presence, and
circular economy model position it uniquely to capture this €175-280M
annual opportunity^³²⁶^.

