€105-175M; Carbon credits (1-1.5M tCO₂e × €50/tCO₂e) = €50-75M;*

*Reduced fertilizer costs (30-40% savings) = €20-30M*

**9. Appendix: Regulatory References**

**CSRD (Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive)**

-   Directive (EU) 2022/2464, Official Journal L 322/15, 16.12.2022

-   Article 19a(2)(e): Value chain sustainability matters disclosure
    mandate

-   Article 29b: Sustainability reporting content requirements

**ESRS (European Sustainability Reporting Standards)**

-   Commission Delegated Regulation (EU) 2023/2772, 31 July 2023

-   ESRS E1: Climate Change (Disclosure E1-6: Gross Scopes 1, 2, 3)

-   ESRS E5: Resource Use & Circular Economy

**EUDR (EU Deforestation Regulation)**

-   Regulation (EU) 2023/1115, Official Journal L 150/206, 09.06.2023

-   Article 3: Due diligence obligations for operators

-   Implementation: 30 December 2025 (large operators)

**GHG Protocol**

-   Corporate Value Chain (Scope 3) Accounting and Reporting Standard
    (2011)

-   Chapter 5: Category 5 - Waste Generated in Operations

-   Land Sector and Removals Guidance (2022)

