# 9.0 EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

CFI\'s BSF bioconversion facility processing 240,000 tonnes of organic
waste annually prevents 229,382 tCO₂e emissions through rapid aerobic
processing that avoids methane generation. The three waste streams -
Empty Fruit Bunches (75,600 tCO₂e), shrimp shells (150,192 tCO₂e), and
chicken manure (3,590 tCO₂e) - each have distinct emission factors based
on their chemical composition, decomposition rates, and baseline
disposal conditions under Verra ACM0022 methodology.

The carbon credit program delivers \$4.59 million in annual revenue at
\$20/tCO₂e baseline pricing, with a 10-year aggregate value of \$45.9
million. Through carbon credit pre-purchase agreements (ERPAs), CFI can
access \$6.9-9.2 million in immediate project finance (15-20% advance),
providing non-dilutive funding for facility construction within 30 days
of contract signature.

**KEY FINDINGS:**

-   **Total Credits:** 229,382 tCO₂e/year across all waste streams

-   **Shrimp Shells Dominance:** 65% of credits despite 42% of volume
    due to 1.49 tCO₂e/t efficiency

-   **BSF vs. Composting:** 99% methane reduction, 12-14 days vs. 60-90
    days

-   **MRV Technology:** LiDAR volumetric measurement with ±5-10%
    accuracy

-   **Project Finance:** \$6.9-9.2M available via 15-20% advance on
    carbon credits

-   **Annual Revenue:** \$4.59M at \$20/tCO₂e, \$45.9M over 10 years

CFI\'s comprehensive MRV system employs industrial LiDAR scanners and
IoT gas sensors to ensure Gold Standard compliance with ±5-10%
measurement accuracy, exceeding the \<10% requirement. The 5-step
operational workflow tracks emissions from waste generation through
final valorization, providing complete digital audit trails for carbon
credit verification.

