**Revenue Coverage**

ERPA upfront (20--30% of Year 1) can fully fund months 6--24 if secured
by Month 5. Net CFI cash requirement drops to \$0--100,000 with strong
ERPA. Annual carbon revenue (Year 2+): \$2,979,000--\$3,750,000 (after
\$30,000--45,000 M&V costs).

**Financing Options Summary**

Self-funded (full revenue): Requires \$88,500--260,000 working capital.
Co-investment split (50/50 with Nestlé): Reduces cost, enables Nestlé
ESG strategy alignment. Impact fund grant (IFC, climate funds): Can
cover 50--100% of costs if approved. Carbon broker pre-financing: Zero
upfront cost; costs brokers 15--25% revenue share.

**Return on Investment**

Initial investment: \$177,000--260,000 (one-time). Annual revenue (Years
2--10): \$2,979,000--\$3,750,000 × 9 years = \$26.8--33.8 million.
10-year ROI: 1,030--1,900% return with payback in less than 1 month via
ERPA upfront.

For investors evaluating CFI\'s viability, the carbon credit pathway
represents a highly attractive incremental revenue stream with proven
market demand, managed certification costs, and exceptional returns once
operational.

